title: Chinese Embassy donates PKR 7 million to Pakistan for quake relief
description: Following the earthquake that hit Pakistan on October 18, 2005, the Chinese Ambassador Zhang Chunxiang presented a donation of 7 million rupees and 2,055 US dollars (personal donation from diplomats) for the President's Earthquake Relief Fund, an earthquake relief fund set up by the government of Pakistan, on behalf of the Chinese companies working in and around Islamabad and personnel of the Embassy to the Foreign Secretary Riaz Mohammad Khan.

title: China donates USD 60,000 in medical facilities to quake-hit Pakistan
description: On 7 December 2005 China signed an agreement for the donation of medical instruments and other facilities worth 60,000 dollars to Pakistan. Present at the ceremony on behalf of their respective governments were Mao Siwei, China's charge d'affaires to Pakistan and Ahmed Jawad, Additional Secretary of Pakistan's Economic Affairs Division. The donation of the medical facilities was among the pledges made by the Chinese government at the international donors' conference held in the Pakistani capital of Islamabad on November 19.

title: China donates 13,000 tents to quake-hit Pakistan
description: Following the flood that hit Pakistan, China donated 13,000 tents as a contribution to flood relief operations. The materials reached Peshawar on 17 November 2005 through a convoy of 163 trucks that had been traveling via Karakoram Highway. The materials were handed over to Pakistan Army by a 13-member Chinese delegation. 7000 tents were dispatched to the quake-hit areas of Azad Kashmir whereas 6000 tents will be distributed in the affected areas of NWPF.
combined_text:

# Title
China donates 13,000 tents to quake-hit Pakistan

# Description
Following the flood that hit Pakistan, China donated 13,000 tents as a contribution to flood relief operations. The materials reached Peshawar on 17 November 2005 through a convoy of 163 trucks that had been traveling via Karakoram Highway. The materials were handed over to Pakistan Army by a 13-member Chinese delegation. 7000 tents were dispatched to the quake-hit areas of Azad Kashmir whereas 6000 tents will be distributed in the affected areas of NWPF.
justification: Project is focused on emergency relief and humanitarian aid without direct environmental or energy transition implications
